---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="FAQ — Nostaliga"
  description="Answers to common questions about Nostaliga: what it is, connecting services, importing archives, privacy, and troubleshooting."
  path="/faq"
>
  <article class="pt-16">
    <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl" style="font-family: var(--font-display);">
      Frequently asked questions
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-6 max-w-2xl text-[color:var(--color-ink-dim)]">
      Quick answers below. If you don't find what you need, the
      <a href="/support">Support page</a> has how to reach us.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-16 text-2xl" style="font-family: var(--font-display);">
      About Nostaliga
    </h2>
    <div class="mt-6 space-y-8 text-[color:var(--color-ink-dim)]">
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg text-[color:var(--color-ink)]">What is Nostaliga?</h3>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Nostaliga reconstructs your personal history — the music you played,
          photos you took, workouts, check-ins, shows you watched, and posts —
          onto a single day-by-day timeline, plus an "On This Day" view that
          resurfaces past moments. Everything is assembled on your device.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg text-[color:var(--color-ink)]">
          Is there an account or login for Nostaliga?
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-2">
          No. Nostaliga has no account and no server of its own. You connect the
          services you want, and everything is stored on your device.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg text-[color:var(--color-ink)]">
          Does Nostaliga work on iPad and Mac?
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Yes — iPhone, iPad, and Mac (Apple Silicon). visionOS support is in
          progress. HealthKit timelines are iPhone-only because HealthKit itself
          is iPhone-only.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="mt-16 text-2xl" style="font-family: var(--font-display);">
      Connecting your data
    </h2>
    <div class="mt-6 space-y-8 text-[color:var(--color-ink-dim)]">
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg text-[color:var(--color-ink)]">
          Which services can I connect?
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Music and activity services connect via their official OAuth flow:
          Spotify, Last.fm, Trakt, Swarm (Foursquare), Strava, and Adobe
          Lightroom. With your permission, Nostaliga also reads Apple Music,
          Photos, HealthKit, and Calendar on-device. Twitter / X, Instagram,
          and Facebook are added by importing the data archive you download from
          each service.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg text-[color:var(--color-ink)]">
          How do I connect Spotify / Last.fm / Trakt / Swarm / Strava /
          Lightroom?
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Open Settings → Integrations, tap the service, and follow the OAuth
          flow. You'll be redirected back to Nostaliga once you authorize. A
          green check appears next to the service when connection is complete.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg text-[color:var(--color-ink)]">
          How do I import Twitter / X, Instagram, or Facebook?
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Those aren't OAuth connections — you download your own data archive
          from each service and add it to Nostaliga. The archive is unpacked and
          processed entirely on your device; Nostaliga never connects to those
          services. Step-by-step instructions for requesting each archive are
          linked from Settings → Integrations.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg text-[color:var(--color-ink)]">
          I connected a service but nothing is showing up.
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Pull to refresh on the main timeline. Background sync also runs
          periodically — open the app once and give it a few minutes on the
          first connection for an initial import.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg text-[color:var(--color-ink)]">
          Background sync isn't running.
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-2">
          iOS controls the schedule — background tasks run when the system
          decides it's a good time (battery, network, usage patterns). Keeping
          Background App Refresh on for Nostaliga in
          <em>iOS Settings → General → Background App Refresh</em> increases how
          often it runs.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="mt-16 text-2xl" style="font-family: var(--font-display);">
      Privacy &amp; your data
    </h2>
    <div class="mt-6 space-y-8 text-[color:var(--color-ink-dim)]">
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg text-[color:var(--color-ink)]">
          Does my data leave the device?
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Only when you explicitly ask Nostaliga to fetch history from a
          third-party service you connected — those requests go directly from
          your device to that service. Matching, correlation, and rendering all
          happen locally. Connecting Spotify, Strava, Trakt, or Swarm also
          relays a short-lived OAuth code through a stateless token-swap endpoint
          so app secrets never ship in the app. See the
          <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a> for the full breakdown.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg text-[color:var(--color-ink)]">
          How do I remove a service's data, or reset the app?
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Data is stored per integration, so there's no single reset button. In
          Settings → Integrations, open a connected service and use
          <em>Delete Imported History</em> to clear its local data and
          <em>Disconnect</em> to remove its access token. To clear everything, do
          that for each service, then delete the app — which removes the
          on-device database and caches.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg text-[color:var(--color-ink)]">
          I want to delete my Nostaliga account.
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-2">
          There is no Nostaliga account to delete — Nostaliga has no server and
          stores nothing about you. To remove local data, disconnect each
          connected service and delete its imported history under
          Settings → Integrations, then uninstall the app. To cut off
          Nostaliga's access to a third-party service from that service's side,
          visit the connected-apps settings on their site (Spotify Apps, Strava
          My Apps, etc.) and revoke Nostaliga.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="mt-16 text-2xl" style="font-family: var(--font-display);">
      Still stuck?
    </h2>
    <div class="mt-6 space-y-8 text-[color:var(--color-ink-dim)]">
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg text-[color:var(--color-ink)]">
          Reporting a bug or requesting a feature.
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Email works best — describe what you did, what you expected, and what
          happened. Screenshots help; a short screen recording is even better.
          Find the address on the <a href="/support">Support page</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
